article.headline: Temple 75, Towson 70
article.story: TOWSON, Md. (AP) -- Dionte Christmas scored a career-high 29 points, Dustin Salisbery added 14 points and 12 rebounds, and Temple defeated Towson 75-70 on Saturday. Mark Tyndale, who was academically ineligible for the Owls' first six games, had 14 points and seven assists in his season debut. Dion Dacons added 10 points for Temple (4-3), which has won three of four. Dennard Abraham led Towson (5-4) with 25 points and nine rebounds. Gary Neal had 20 points, and C.C. Williams scored 11 for the Tigers, who had a two-game winning streak snapped. Towson used a strong man-to-man defense to whittle away a 12-point second-half deficit, and got within 68-65 on a pair of free throws by Neal with 57 seconds remaining. But two free throws by Tyndale with 46.6 seconds to go put the Owls ahead by five. A pair of foul shots by Christmas made it 73-67 with 16.9 seconds left. Tim Crossin hit a 3-pointer from the right wing to get the Tigers within 73-70 with 3.5 seconds on the clock, but Tyndale sealed the victory by converting two free throws with 3 seconds remaining. Christmas scored 14 points in the opening 20 minutes, six coming on a pair of 3-pointers in an early 10-0 run that produced a 16-6 Owls lead. Towson, coming off an 11-day layoff, missed 17 of its first 21 shots from the floor and weathered a first-half drought of 6:06 without a field goal. But the Tigers closed the half on a 16-6 burst and trailed 38-30 at halftime. Williams had six points during the run, twice scoring on transition layups.
